      "content": "okay, but wont my prof call me out if i just focus on the negative side? it feels like u're saying nationalism is mostly just a tool for oppression. if i wanted to present a balanced view, wouldnt i have to admit that for many people, having that national bond is what makes them feel secure and connected to their history? isnt it possible that the \"danger\" u're talking about is just a subset of it, and the core of it is actually something good? u seem pretty set on the idea that it's something we should recognize as a problem rather than a tool for stability.",
